San'i, also known as "scattered officials" or "scattered ranks," referred to individuals who held a {{ill|court rank|ja|位階}} but did not occupy an official {{ill|government post|ja|官職}}. San'i included divisions of {{ill|Kyōkan|ja|京官}} (metropolitan officials) and {{ill|Gekan|ja|外官}} (provincial officials) as well as {{ill|monkan|ja|文官}} (civil officials) and {{ill|bukan|ja|武官}} (military officials). Most San'i were retirees.
San'i of the fifth rank or higher worked full-time ({{ill|Chōjō|ja|長上}}) at the San'iryō. Those of the sixth rank and below who lived in the capital rotated duties ({{ill|Bunban|ja|分番}}) at the San'iryō, while others performed similar duties at provincial offices ({{ill|Kokufu|ja|国府}}). These duties included assisting other government offices and acting as messengers. Military San'i (武散位), on the other hand, were also managed by the {{ill|Hyōbu-shō|ja|兵部省}}.
Additionally, the San'iryō managed the {{ill|Chōshūshi|ja|朝集使}}, one of the {{ill|Shido no tsukai|ja|四度使}} (four types of messengers), while they were stationed in the capital. As the San'i system became increasingly symbolic, the institution's importance declined, leading to its merger with the Shikibu-shō in {{ill|Kanpyō|ja|寛平}} 8 (896). Thereafter, the Shikibu-shō took over the management of San'i affairs.
== Staff == * {{ill|Head (Tō)|ja|頭}} (equivalent to {{ill|Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|ja|従五位下}}) – 1 position * {{ill|Assistant (Suke)|ja|助}} (equivalent to {{ill|Junior Sixth Rank, Upper Grade|ja|従六位上}}) – 1 position * {{ill|Secretary (Yō)|ja|允}} (equivalent to {{ill|Junior Seventh Rank, Lower Grade|ja|従七位下}}) – 1 position * {{ill|Senior Clerk (Daizoku)|ja|大属}} (equivalent to {{ill|Junior Eighth Rank, Lower Grade|ja|従八位下}}) – 1 position * {{ill|Junior Clerk (Shōzoku)|ja|少属}} (equivalent to {{ill|Greater Initial Rank, Upper Grade|ja|大初位上}}) – 1 position * {{ill|Shishō|ja|史生}} – Initially 6 positions, later reduced to 4 * {{ill|San'i|ja|散位}} * {{ill|Shibu (servants)|ja|使部}} * {{ill|Shichō|ja|仕丁}}
== Related Topics == * {{ill|Officials (kanjin)|ja|官人}}
