'''San'iryō''' (散位寮) was one of the institutions under the [[:en:Shikibu-shō|Ministry of Ceremonial Affairs]] in the [[:en:Ritsuryō|Ritsuryō system]] of ancient [[:en:Japan|Japan]]. Notably, there was no equivalent institution to San'iryō in the Tang dynasty system.
== Responsibilities == The San'iryō managed the {{ill|San'i|ja|散位|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/San'i|qq=}} (unassigned officials) through a roster system and conducted evaluations of their service.
San'i, also known as "scattered officials" or "scattered Ranks," referred to individuals who held a {{ill|court Rank|ja|位階|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/court Rank|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} but did not occupy an official {{ill|government post|ja|官職|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/government post|qq=}}. San'i included divisions of {{ill|Kyōkan|ja|京官|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kyōkan|qq=}} (metropolitan officials) and {{ill|Gekan|ja|外官|1=Gaikan|lt=Local officials (Gaikan)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gekan|13=User:Immanuelle/Gaikan|qq=}} (provincial officials) as well as {{ill|monkan|ja|文官|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/monkan|qq=}} (civil officials) and {{ill|bukan|ja|武官|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/bukan|qq=}} (military officials). Most San'i were retirees.
San'i of the fifth Rank or higher worked full-time ({{ill|Chōjō|ja|長上|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chōjō|qq=}}) at the San'iryō. Those of the sixth Rank and below who lived in the capital rotated duties ({{ill|Bunban|ja|分番|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bunban|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) at the San'iryō, while others performed similar duties at provincial offices ([[:en:Kokufu|Kokufu]]). These duties included assisting other government offices and acting as messengers. Military San'i (武散位), on the other hand, were also managed by the [[:en:Ministry of War (pre-modern Japan)|Ministry of War]].
Additionally, the San'iryō managed the {{ill|Chōshūshi|ja|朝集使|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chōshūshi|qq=}}, one of the {{ill|Shido no tsukai|ja|四度使|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shido no tsukai|qq=}} (four types of messengers), while they were stationed in the capital. As the San'i system became increasingly symbolic, the institution's importance declined, leading to its merger with the Shikibu-shō in [[:en:Kanpyō (era)|Kanpyō]] 8 (896). Thereafter, the Shikibu-shō took over the management of San'i affairs.
== Staff == * [[:en:Head|Head (Tō)]] (equivalent to {{ill|Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|ja|従五位下|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fifth Rank|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 従五位}}) – 1 position * {{ill|Assistant (Suke)|ja|助|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Assistant (Suke)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (equivalent to {{ill|Junior Sixth Rank, Upper Grade|ja|従六位上|1=Junior Sixth Rank|lt=Junior Sixth Rank, Upper Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Sixth Rank, Upper Grade|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Sixth Rank|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 従六位}}) – 1 position * {{ill|Secretary (Yō)|ja|允|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Secretary (Yō)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 寮 (律令制)}} (equivalent to {{ill|Junior Seventh Rank, Lower Grade|ja|従七位下|1=Junior Seventh Rank|lt=Junior Seventh Rank, Lower Grade|3=従七位|1=Junior Seventh Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Seventh Rank, Lower Grade|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Seventh Rank|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 従七位}}) – 1 position * {{ill|Senior Clerk (Daizoku)|ja|大属|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Clerk (Daizoku)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (equivalent to {{ill|Junior Eighth Rank, Lower Grade|ja|従八位下|1=Junior Eighth Rank|lt=Junior Eighth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Eighth Rank, Lower Grade|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Eighth Rank|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 従八位}}) – 1 position * {{ill|Junior Clerk (Shōzoku)|ja|少属|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Clerk (Shōzoku)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (equivalent to {{ill|Greater Initial Rank, Upper Grade|ja|大初位上|1=Greater Initial Rank|lt=Greater Initial Rank, Upper Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Greater Initial Rank, Upper Grade|13=User:Immanuelle/Greater Initial Rank|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 大初位}}) – 1 position * {{ill|Shishō|ja|史生|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shishō|qq=}} – Initially 6 positions, later reduced to 4 * {{ill|San'i|ja|散位|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/San'i|qq=}} * {{ill|Shibu (servants)|ja|使部|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shibu (servants)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} * {{ill|Shichō|ja|仕丁|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shichō|qq=}} == See Also == * {{ill|Officials (kanjin)|ja|官人|1=Kanjin|2=ja|3=官人|4=ko|5=관인|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Officials (kanjin)|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanjin|qq=}}
